<item>
            <title>[SOLR-230] make post.jar support better args for using tutorial</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-230</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-86&quot; title=&quot;[PATCH]  standalone updater cli based on httpClient&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-86&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-86&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; create post.jar which eliminated the need for post.sh ... but as noticed in &lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-164&quot; title=&quot;Use the SOLR-86 client in examples of the Solr tutorial&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-164&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-164&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; there are still some cases in the tutorial that require direct use of curl (deleting) and there are some nice things about post.sh that post.jar doesn&apos;t support (defaulting the URL)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;this issue is to tackle some of the ideas Bertrand and I posted as a comment in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-86&quot; title=&quot;[PATCH]  standalone updater cli based on httpClient&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-86&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-86&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; after it was resolved....&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Bertrand Delacretaz &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;19/Feb/07 12:35 AM&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; ...&lt;br/&gt;
Considering the tutorial examples (&lt;a href=&quot;http://lucene.apache.org/solr/tutorial.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://lucene.apache.org/solr/tutorial.html&lt;/a&gt;), it&apos;d be useful to allow this to POST its standard input, or the contents of a command-line parameter: ...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Hoss Man &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;19/Feb/07 11:50 AM&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
yeah ... i think we should hardcode &lt;a href=&quot;http://localhost:8983/solr/update&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://localhost:8983/solr/update&lt;/a&gt; with a possible override by system prop, then add either a command line switch other another system prop indicating to use the command line as filenames or as raw data, and another op for stdin.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;java -jar -Ddata=files post.jar *.xml&lt;br/&gt;
java -jar post.jar *.xml ... data=files being the default&lt;br/&gt;
echo &quot;&amp;lt;delete&amp;gt;&amp;lt;query&amp;gt;name:DDR&amp;lt;/query&amp;gt;&amp;lt;/delete&amp;gt;&quot; | java -jar -Ddata=stdin post.jar&lt;br/&gt;
cat *.xml | java -jar -Ddata=stdin post.jar&lt;br/&gt;
java -jar -Ddata=args post.jar &quot;&amp;lt;delete&amp;gt;&amp;lt;query&amp;gt;name:DDR&amp;lt;/query&amp;gt;&amp;lt;/delete&amp;gt;&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
java -jar -Durl=&lt;a href=&quot;http://localhost:8983/solr/update&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://localhost:8983/solr/update&lt;/a&gt; post.jar *.xml &lt;/p&gt;</description>
